@startuml PY-010-sequence
title PY-010 — Number Guessing Game · Sequence: Project Complete → Badge Awarded

actor Learner
participant "ProjectShell\n«client»" as Shell
participant "useSkillProgress\n«hook»" as SkillHook
participant "getProjectContent()\n«lib»" as GetData
participant "ProjectCodePanel\n«client»" as CodePanel
participant "pyodide.runCode()\n«lib»" as Pyodide
participant "useProjectProgress\n«hook»" as ProjHook
participant "localStorage" as Store

== Page Load ==

Learner -> Shell : navigate to /projects/pj-3
Shell -> SkillHook : isUnlocked("pj-3")?
SkillHook -> Store : read skill completions
Store --> SkillHook : variables=mid✓ loops=mid✓ conditions=mid✓
SkillHook --> Shell : unlocked = true
Shell -> GetData : getProjectContent("pj-3")
GetData --> Shell : { scaffoldedCode, solution, expectedKeywords: ["Got it"], ... }
Shell --> CodePanel : render(scaffoldedCode)
CodePanel --> Learner : editor pre-filled with game loop stubs

== Attempt Loop ==

loop until "Got it" in output or 3 failed attempts

  Learner -> CodePanel : fills in guess check + hints, clicks Run
  CodePanel -> Pyodide : runCode(learnerCode)
  Pyodide --> CodePanel : { output, rawError }

  alt output contains "Got it" (case-insensitive)
    CodePanel -> ProjHook : markComplete("pj-3", xpReward=300)
    ProjHook -> Store : save project completion
    CodePanel --> Learner : ProjectBadge 🎯 + XPRewardBanner (+300 XP)\n+ ConceptSummary revealed
  else failed attempt
    CodePanel -> ProjHook : incrementAttempts()
    alt attempts >= 3
      CodePanel --> Learner : Show solution button
    else
      CodePanel --> Learner : try again
    end
  end

end

@enduml
